        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 10:16AM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 1016 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Owendale, or 7 miles southeast of Sebewaing, moving northeast at 35
mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bad Axe, Cass City, Sebewaing, Harbor Beach, Ubly, Port Hope, Elkton,
Kinde, Gagetown, Owendale, Verona, Helena, Minden, Redman,
Parisville, White Rock, Ivanhoe, Rapson, New Greenleaf, and Ruth.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
